# .zprofile is sourced on login shells and before .zshrc. As a general rule, it should not change the
# shell environment at all.

# .zprofile — login-shell one-shot setup, sourced before .zshrc.
#
# brew shellenv used to live here, but .zprofile is only read by login shells.
# Non-login shells (nvim :terminal, scripts, cron, `$(cmd)` subshells) never see
# it, which made `which opencode` diverge between tmux windows and nvim
# terminals. The block has moved to ~/.zshenv so every shell mode gets the
# linuxbrew PATH. Keep this file for future login-only init: ssh-agent,
# gpg-agent, keychain tokens, etc.
